name: GDG Freshers Meetup
description: This is an event directed at new members of GDG Bingham University designed to motivate and inspire them with a massive arsenal of technological tools.

name: Google I/O 2017 Extended - Bingham University
description:
If you missed the just concluded Google I/O 2017 in San Francisco, then join us as we will be showing the Keynote and other sessions by expert developers within and outside our community. There will be Tech talks, Codelabs and more. Visit our website (http://bhu.gdg.ng) for more details.﻿

Note: All codelabs require a Laptop and if you will like to participate in any of the codelabs, kindly remember to come with one.

name: GDG Bingham University Organizers Meeting
description: This is our monthly organizers meeting where we come together to discuss various strategies for organizing our events. If you will like to meet with our organizers and offer recommendations, please stop by as we will love to get your inputs on how to make our events better. There will be lots of drinks and food so bring your creative hats with you :)

name: GDG Rookie I/O
description: We always find a way to welcome our new students to the GDG community and this time it's no different. Join us on the 4th of November, 2017 as we welcome our Freshers to this wonderful and awesome developer community.

name: North Central DevFest 2017
description:
North Central DevFest is our annual all-day Developer Festival focusing on Google recent technological trends including but not limited to the following:

- Mobile Development (Android and Tooling)

- UI/UX Featuring Material Design

- Web/PWA/AMP/Firebase

- Google Cloud

- Machine Learning (TensorFlow, Vision API)

North Central DevFest 2017 will be organized as a typical DevFest in the Month of November featuring Speakers from our cluster of participating chapters and the community at large to attain a bigger impact in the developer community.
